ity":"Common"},{"title":"Prior refusals not addressed","description":"Ireland or other refusals hidden in application.","fix":"Disclose and explain changed circumstances","severity":"High"},{"title":"Document quality","description":"Blurry scans, wrong translations, or inconsistent names.","fix":"Certified translations; consistent naming across docs","severity":"Medium"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee Student visa approval?","a":"No. Irish Immigration Service Delivery assesses each application. Strong CAS and funds help but approval is never guaranteed."},{"q":"How much funds for London vs outside London?","a":"Living costs differ—verify current amounts on irishimmigration.ie. Plus remaining tuition after deposit shown on CAS."},{"q":"What is the 28-day rule?","a":"Funds must remain at or above required amount for 28 consecutive days ending no more than 31 days before application."},{"q":"Can spouse join on Student visa?","a":"Dependants allowed only if course meets specific criteria (e.g., postgraduate level certain duration). Check current rules."},{"q":"Is IELTS Irish Immigration Service Delivery mandatory?","a":"If SELT required, must be Irish Immigration Service Delivery-approved test from approved centre. Some nationals/courses may be exempt."},{"q":"When to apply?","a":"Up to 6 months before course start if applying from outside Ireland. Do not apply without valid CAS."},{"q":"Can student work?","a":"Limited hours during term; rules on irishimmigration.ie. Cannot work as professional sportsperson or doctor in training."},{"q":"What after course completion?","a":"Discuss Graduate Route eligibility separately—requires successful completion at eligible institution."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Student Route visa for study at a Ireland institution holding a valid sponsor licence. Requires Confirmation of Acceptance for Studies (CAS) and online Irish Immigration Service Delivery application."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this serv